      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="365-0203" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1724.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">D</hi>EAR Sir, I think 'tis doubly hard,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-2"> Your Ears and Doors should both be barr'd:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-3"> Can any thing be more unkind?</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-4"> Must I not see, 'cause you are blind?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-5"> Methinks, a Friend at Night should cheer you,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-6"> A Friend that loves to see and hear you:</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-7"> Why am I robb'd of that Delight?</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-8"> When you can be no Loser by't.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-9"> Nay, when 'tis plain, for what is plainer?</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-10"> That, if you heard, you'd be no Gainer.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-11"> For sure, you are not yet to learn,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-12"> That Hearing is not your Concern.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-13"> Then be your Doors no longer barr'd,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-365-0203-line-14"> Your Business, Sir, is to be heard.365-0203   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
